The busy bees of Alberta

Production and value of Canadian honey from 1924 to 2021

Published

May 1, 2023

 

Statistics Canada has wonderfully surveyed honey producers across the provinces for over 50 years. To promote transparency and accountability within the industry, the data can provide insights into the current state of the industry and help producers make informed decisions about how to manage their operations.

 

The data collected

 

  • How many colonies there are in the province.
  • How much honey is produced in the province.
  • How many Beekeepers there are in the province.
  • The value of the honey sold connected to the provinces capacity.

 

Provinces

 

  • Ontario
  • Quebec
  • New Brunswick
  • Nova Scotia
  • British Columbia
  • Alberta
  • Prince Edward Island
  • Manitoba
  • Saskatchewan

 

Canada’s 2022 honey industry

 

  • Colonies decreased by 8 %.
  • Production decreased by 16 %.
  • Production by colony decreased by 8 %.
  • Beekeepers increased by 3 %.
  • Value decreased by 6 %.

 



The trimuvate of honey production in Canada is Alberta, gaining double the value; Manitoba; And Saskatchewan.The former group accounts for four-fifths of Canadas Total Honey Production. While greater colonies do produce more value, Manitoba's and Saskatchewan's strength in optimization is awesome.





Colonies, production, and value are strongly, positively, correlated.

Alberta’s capacity

Colonies

 

 

  • 40 % of Canada’s bee colonies are in Alberta.
  • Alberta’s colonies decreased by 7 % over the last year.

 

Pounds

 

The value in pounds is reduced by 1000

  • 40 % of Canada’s honey production is in Alberta.
  • Alberta’s production decreased by 11 % over the last year.

 

Yield per colony

 

 

  • Alberta’s yield is optimized to produce 4% than the national average.
  • Alberta’s yield decreased by 4 % over the last year.

 

Beekeepers

 

 

  • 12 % of Canada’s beekeepers are in Alberta.
  • Alberta’s beekeepers decreased by 3 % over the last year.

 

Dollars

 

The dollar value is reduced by 1000

  • 37 % of Canada’s honey sales are from Albertan producers.
  • Alberta’s sales increased by 2 % over the last year.
